<DOC><DOCNO>  ZF207-472-666  </DOCNO><DOCID>07 472 666.andO;</DOCID><JOURNAL>MIS Week  July 31 1989 v10 n30 p13(1).andM;</JOURNAL><TITLE>Group forms to promote fiber-optic LANs; FDDI promises fastertransmission over wider areas. (the Advanced Networking Group)(fiber distributed data interface)</TITLE><AUTHOR>Klopp, Charlotte.andM;</AUTHOR><TEXT><ABSTRACT>Advanced Micro Devices Inc spearheads the Advanced NetworkingGroup (ANG), a group of 37 high-tech companies aiming to promotethe fiber distributed data interface (FDDI).andP;  FDDI is a high-speedtransmission standard for local area networks (LANs) holding thepromise of transmitting data at 100M-bps.andP;  It also entails widerconnectivity between mainframes and supercomputers, and increasedgeographical transmission range.andP;  The higher transmission speedsof fiber optics will facilitate motion and flow systems as well asother high-powered graphics applications.andP;  As many as 500stations, ranging from microcomputers to mainframes, can beconfigured on a single FDDI network.andM;</ABSTRACT></TEXT><DESCRIPT>Company:   Advanced Micro Devices Inc. (planning).andO;Ticker:    AMD.andO;Topic:     Advanced Networking GroupFiber Distributed Data Interface StandardComputer IndustryLocal Area NetworksFiber OpticsApplicationsGoals and Objectives.andM;</DESCRIPT></DOC>